10/08/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Turkish institutions have decided to recognise Kosovo passports, the Turkish Embassy in Pristina announced on Friday (August 8th).
Starting on Monday, Turkey will start issuing visas based on the passports and Kosovo citizens will be able to enter Turkey with the documents.
Turkey was among the first countries to recognise Kosovo's independence, which was declared unilaterally on February 17th.
Sweden's Foreign Ministry also announced on Friday that it is recognising the new passports.
(Telegrafi - 09/08/08;
Makfax, Beta, B92 - 08/08/08)
